B.EI=new A.o("Term: Contrecoup contusion","Definition: A contusion occurring on the side opposite the point of impact due to brain rebounding.")
B.DY=new A.o("Why are the inferior frontal lobes and anterior temporal tips the most common locations for contusions?","The rough bony surfaces of the anterior and middle cranial fossae.")
B.Ha=new A.o("What is the typical clinical presentation of orbitofrontal contusions?","Personality changes, disinhibition, and impaired social judgment.")
B.EB=new A.o("Temporal tip contusions are primarily associated with deficits in _____.","Memory and emotional regulation.")
B.Hn=new A.o("What is the 'blossoming' window for brain contusions requiring serial CT monitoring?","24-72 hours.")
B.Ge=new A.o("What is the most common vascular source of an epidural hematoma (EDH)?","Middle meningeal artery.")
B.H6=new A.o("What is the characteristic CT appearance of an epidural hematoma?","Biconvex or lens-shaped hyperdensity.")
B.EE=new A.o("How do epidural hematomas relate to cranial suture lines on imaging?","They do not cross suture lines.")
B.GC=new A.o("Which focal hemorrhage type is characterized by a crescent shape that crosses suture lines but not the midline falx?","Subdural hematoma (SDH).")
B.E_=new A.o("What is the primary vascular source of a subdural hematoma?","Torn bridging veins.")
B.Gl=new A.o("At what time interval does a subdural hematoma appear isodense on a CT scan?","3 days to 3 weeks (Subacute phase).")
B.FH=new A.o("What secondary complications are associated with traumatic subarachnoid hemorrhage (SAH)?","Vasospasm and communicating hydrocephalus.")
B.GT=new A.o("What is the leading cause of morbidity and prolonged unconsciousness in TBI?","Diffuse Axonal Injury (DAI).")
B.Fx=new A.o("Axonal injury in DAI is primarily a result of secondary axotomy caused by cytoskeletal disruption and _____.","Calcium-mediated proteolysis.")
B.Ft=new A.o("Why does myelin debris actively inhibit remyelination after TBI?","It blocks oligodendrocyte progenitor cell (OPC) differentiation.")
B.GH=new A.o("Which receptor mediates the suppression of axon regeneration by myelin-associated inhibitors like Nogo-A?","NgR1 receptor.")
B.DT=new A.o("Term: Retraction balls","Definition: Swollen proximal stumps of disconnected axons that serve as the pathognomonic hallmark of DAI.")
B.Hz=new A.o("Which immunohistochemical stain is used to visualize retraction balls in DAI?","Beta-amyloid precursor protein (beta-APP).")
