B.Hy=new A.o("How long does metabolic recovery typically take in the adult brain following a concussion?","7-10 days.")
B.DO=new A.o("Which type of cerebral edema is characterized by Na+/K+ ATPase failure and intracellular swelling?","Cytotoxic edema.")
B.G5=new A.o("Why are steroids contraindicated in the management of severe TBI?","They do not treat cytotoxic edema and were shown to increase mortality in the CRASH trial.")
B.Eu=new A.o("Term: Ferroptosis","Definition: An iron-dependent form of regulated cell death driven by lipid peroxidation.")
B.Ez=new A.o("Which enzyme is the key inhibitor of ferroptosis by preventing lipid ROS accumulation?","Glutathione peroxidase 4 (GPX4).")
B.HA=new A.o("During which time frame post-TBI does the M2 (anti-inflammatory) microglial phenotype typically peak?","Days 3-5.")
B.FJ=new A.o("At what point post-injury does the M1 (pro-inflammatory) microglial phenotype begin to dominate?","Day 7.")
B.ES=new A.o("What is the biphasic timeline for blood-brain barrier (BBB) disruption after TBI?","Initial disruption at 3-6 hours and a second wave at 1-3 days.")
B.E3=new A.o("What percentage of late TBI survivors (>1 year) demonstrate persistent, widespread BBB disruption?","47%.")
